<div class="poem-ec">
	<div>What you call consciousness is the sum<br>
	of colours reflected off many mirrors.<br> 
	Your memories are as distant as dreams,<br>
	and when you cannot remember, you invent<br>
	fictions that become more brilliant with each<br>
	utterance, sheltered from the rain.</div>

	<div>You are changing, and yet you fear change:<br> 
	you prefer the stream from which you drink<br>			
	and reflect to be still.<br>
	If there were no mirrors,<br>
	I would lay by the lakes,<br>
	and if all the waters were rapid,<br>
	I would carve myself in stone.</div> 

	<div>We see our own reflection over<br>
	the circumference of our eyes.<br>
	What a terrible fate for a man<br>
	who hates the sight of himself.</div>
</div>


